188A 101st Legislative Session 188
2026 South Dakota Legislature
Senate Bill 188
AMENDME NT 188A
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Senator Carley
1 An Act to revise public notice requirements for new sand, gravel, and construction
2 aggregate mines.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
4 Section 1. That § 45-6-68 be AMENDED:
5 45-6-68. The operator shall must publish notice of each mine mining operation
6 once in a newspaper of general circulation in the locality of the operation, at least fourteen
7 days before the commencement of mining, if the operation will affect an area of ten acres
8 or less, or will annually extract less than twenty-five thousand tons of material.
9 If the operation will affect an area greater than ten acres, or annually extract at
10 least twenty-five thousand tons of material, the operator must publish notice of each mine
11 operation at least three times in a newspaper of general circulation in the locality of the
12 operation. The first notice must be published no sooner than one hundred eighty days
13 before the commencement of the mining operation. The second notice must be published
14 at least ninety days before the commencement of the mining operation. The third notice
15 must be published at least thirty days before the commencement of the mining operation.
16 The notice shall contain the must:
17 (1) State the identity and address of the operator and resident agent, the;
18 (2) State the location of the mining operation, whether;
19 (3) State whether the mineral to be mined is sand, gravel, or rock to be crushed and
20 used in construction, the ;
21 (4) State whether the mining operation is to involve the use of explosives;
22 (5) Include any plans to mitigate dust, stormwater runoff, and noise from the
23 operation;
24 (6) State the dates of commencement and completion of the operation, the;
25 (7) Describe any proposed future use of the affected land; and the location
26 (8) Indicate where additional information about the operation may be obtained.
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

