1 Section 2. That § 45-6-69 be AMENDED:
2 45-6-69. The operator of a mining operation that affects an area of ten acres or
3 less, or extracts less than twenty-five thousand tons of material, shall submit notification,
4 consisting of forward all information required in § 45-6-68, together with a map of the
5 affected area and the information required in the newspaper notice to the South Dakota,
6 to the persons listed in this section at least fourteen days before the commencement of
7 mining.
8 The operator of a mining operation that affects an area greater than ten acres, or
9 annually extracts at least twenty-five thousand tons of material, shall forward all
10 information required in § 45-6-68, together with a map of the affected area, to the persons
11 listed in this section at least ninety one hundred eighty days before the commencement
12 of mining. The information must be forwarded to:
13 (1) The Department of Agriculture and Natural Resources, the South Dakota;
14 (2) The Department of Game, Fish and Parks, the South Dakota;
15 (3) The Department of Education, and the local conservation district, of the operator's
16 intent to commence mining at a new mine site at least thirty days before beginning
17 mining operations;
18 (4) The conservation district within which the mining site is located;
19 (5) Any individual who lives within a two-mile radius of the center of the mine site and
20 who can be reached by direct mail;
21 (6) The board of commissioners for the county in which the proposed mining operation
22 is located;
23 (7) The governing board of any municipality located within ten miles of the site of the
24 proposed mining operation;
25 (8) Any broadcast media located in the county where the proposed mining operation
26 is located; and
27 (9) Any statewide public notice website maintained by a media organization in this
28 state.
29 Section 3. That § 45-6-70 be AMENDED:
30 45-6-70. When an emergency situation exists and when in the public interest, the
31 secretary of agriculture and natural resources may waive the minimum fourteen-day
32 advertising requirements and thirty-day notice requirement of §§ time period applicable
